	(text "Notes\n1. GPIO7 is used to enable the reference voltage just before reading the voltage across\n   the thermister. This eliminates self heating which is probably not much of a problem.\n2. At 0°C the voltage across the thermister is just above 1.0V which means the \n   1.024V range is good for room temperature readings.\n3. The wire colors on the I^{2}C Temp Sensor are for the FS200 and FS304.\n3. +5V is not used on this board."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 18.796 172.466 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.905 1.905)
				(thickness 0.381)
				(bold yes)
				(color 0 132 0 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "f9b300dc-becb-4be3-9749-4f23b22fb9b3")
	)
